FBIS4-33407 "drlat109_b_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Forms National Crisis Commission Forms National Crisis Commission FL0606183994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 GMT 6 Jun 94 FL0606183994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] In order to face the sanctions and the total embargo, the government has formed a National Crisis Commission. By decree, the government of Judge Emile Jonassaint announced on Saturday 4 June the formation of a crisis commission in charge of managing the embargo and guaranteeing the rights of the population to food and work. The commission is also in charge of assessing the consequences of the embargo and is presided over by the minister of finances and economy.
